UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1640
1 disciplines, including:
2 (a) Track, signal, and train control;
3 (b) Motive power and equipment;
4 (c) Operating practices compliance;
5 (d) Hazardous material; and
6 (e) Highway-rail grade crossings.
7 (5) To the extent allowed by the Federal Railroad Administration and authorized by
8 the cabinet, an inspector may issue citations for violations of administrative
9 regulations adopted pursuant to this section to ensure railroad employees and
10 public safety and welfare.
11 (6) The cabinet shall promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with KRS
12 Chapter 13A to carry out the provisions of this section.
13 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 174 IS CREATED TO
14 READ AS FOLLOWS:
15 (1) The Railroad Transportation Advisory Board is established as an advisory body to
16 the executive and legislative branches of government on matters pertaining to rail
17 transportation.
18 (2) The Railroad Transportation Advisory Board shall be composed of seven (7)
19 members, to be appointed as follows:
20 (a) Four (4) members representing railroads in the Commonwealth, to be
21 appointed by the Governor from a list of nine (9) nominees, with a list of
22 three (3) nominees each supplied by:
23 1. The Kentucky Railroad Association;
24 2. A major railroad operating in Kentucky; and
25 3. An organized rail labor organization.
26 In appointing members under subparagraph 1. of this paragraph, the
27 Governor shall give consideration to including two (2) representatives from
Page 2 of 4
XXXX 2/11/2026 12:19 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1640
1 railroad management and two (2) representatives from railroad union
2 labor;
3 (b) Two (2) at-large members who are not employed by a railroad and who
4 reside in a county or counties where a rail carrier operates, to be appointed
5 by the Governor from a list of six (6) nominees, with a list of three (3)
6 nominees each supplied by:
7 1. The Kentucky Association of Counties; and
8 2. The Kentucky League of Cities; and
9 (c) One (1) member of the Transportation Cabinet to be appointed by the
10 secretary of the Transportation Cabinet.
11 (3) After the initial appointments, members of the Railroad Transportation Advisory
12 Board shall serve terms of four (4) years. Members shall be eligible to succeed
13 themselves and shall serve until their successor is appointed.
14 (4) Members of the Railroad Transportation Advisory Board shall not be paid for
15 their services as board members and shall not be reimbursed for any expenses
16 involved in attending board meetings.
17 (5) The Railroad Transportation Advisory Board shall elect a chair and a vice chair
18 from its members who shall serve in those capacities until replaced. A majority of
19 the board shall constitute a quorum for the purposes of conducting business. The
20 board shall be subject to the provisions of the Kentucky Open Records Act, KRS
21 61.870 to 61.884.
22 (6) The Railroad Transportation Advisory Board shall meet biennially, or when
23 called by the chair, or at the request of the secretary of the Transportation
24 Cabinet. The board shall receive assistance in carrying out its administrative
25 functions from the Transportation Cabinet and shall be attached to the
26 Transportation Cabinet for administrative purposes.
27 (7) The Railroad Transportation Advisory Board shall:
Page 3 of 4
XXXX 2/11/2026 12:19 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1640
1 (a) Advise the Transportation Cabinet, the Governor's Office, and the General
2 Assembly on matters relating to rail transportation;
3 (b) Identify initiatives and priorities to reduce the frequency of blocked
4 highway rail crossings, improve emergency preparedness and resilience,
5 and improve rail safety;
6 (c) Evaluate the use of technology to detect and address mechanical and other
7 issues to reduce the risk of derailments, accidents, and other incidents; and
8 (d) Assess the Commonwealth's participation in a state rail safety inspection
9 program.
